
Overview of verb bask

The verb bask has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (3) enjoy, bask, relish, savor, savour -- (derive or receive pleasure from; get enjoyment from; take pleasure in; "She relished her fame and basked in her glory")
2. (2) bask -- (be exposed; "The seals were basking in the sun")
